Brendan Herron - Attorney Biography -  Wilson Sonsini Goodrich & Rosati




               BRENDAN HERRONAssociateCorporateEXPERIENCE: Brendan Herron is an associate at Wilson Sonsini Goodrich & Rosati in the firm's SOMA office, a collaborative workspace that serves entrepreneurs and early-stage businesses, as well as the angel and venture capital investors that fund them. Brendan's practice focuses on representing and advising tech start-ups, early-stage and emerging companies, founders, venture capital funds, and angel investors on corporate and business issues, including venture financings, strategic transactions and M&A, technology transactions, and high-value commercial deals. Prior to joining the firm, Brendan spent time at Kirkland & Ellis in Chicago, where he represented private equity funds and their portfolio companies in M&A transactions, IPOs, leveraged buyouts, take-privates, restructurings, and other strategic transactions, and Silicon Legal Strategy in San Francisco, where he represented start-ups and venture capital and angel investors in venture financings, M&A, and corporate matters.     EDUCATION:    J.D., University of Michigan Law School, 2009 Associate Editor, Michigan Telecommunications & Technology Law Review; Member, Business Law Association   A.B., Duke University, 2002     ADMISSIONS:    State Bar of California   State Bar of Illinois       Contact Information 139 Townsend StreetSuite 150San Francisco, CA 94107Phone | 415/471-3959Fax | 866-974-7329Email | Brendan Herronbherron@wsgr.com   Areas of ExpertiseCapital MarketsCorporate GovernanceMergers & AcquisitionsPrivate Company RepresentationPublic Company RepresentationStart-Ups and Venture Capital Print to PDF    Attorney Advertising  |  Privacy Policy  |  Terms of Use  |  Contact Us  |  Mailing List Signup  |  Copyright © 2017 WSGRMarketing Automation Platform 
                 




